    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Social Security, as Seen at 19 and 65</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William Hohri letter questions whether individual investments will outperform Social Security; cites experience of private pension plans (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Presents Social Security as Crucial Test'' (front page, May 16): One question should warn those who think that individual investments will outperform Social Security: what private pension plan, with its carefully managed investments, has been able to provide cost-of-living increases to its beneficiaries?</p>
        <p>WILLIAM HOHRI  Lomita, Calif., May 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
